        <div class="bento-cta">See full review <span class="arrow">↓</span></div>
      </a>

      <a class="bento-card" href="#service-4">
        <div class="bento-num">04</div>
        <h3 class="bento-title">Best reviews: Birdeye</h3>
        <h4 class="bento-sub">For busy practices that need <span class="accent">automated post-visit review requests</span> at scale.</h4>
        <p class="bento-desc">Automated review requests via text/email after patient visits, plus AI response drafting — from $299/mo.</p>
        <div class="bento-cta">See full review <span class="arrow">↓</span></div>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- METHODOLOGY -->
  <section class="problem-section">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">How we tested</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">We tested <span class="accent">10 tools</span> against five dental-specific criteria.</h2>
      <p>No affiliate fluff. Consistent Google Business Profile activity, blog content targeting dental keywords, patient reviews, and clean directory listings — these are what drive rankings for dental practices. We measured every tool against these benchmarks.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ba-grid">
      <div class="ba-col before">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">What we measured</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">5 dental-specific criteria.</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">Same scorecard across all 10 tools.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h4>GBP management</h4>
              <p>"Dentist near me" searches pull from GBP. Can the tool create or optimize Google Business Profile content?</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Content creation</h4>
              <p>Does it produce blog articles about dental topics? Blog content ranks for "teeth whitening cost," "emergency dentist [city]," and hundreds of long-tail dental queries.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Review management</h4>
              <p>Does it generate and manage patient reviews? Patients read 7–10 reviews before choosing a dentist. Reviews impact local pack ranking directly.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">04</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Local rank tracking</h4>
              <p>Does it track rankings for dental keywords in your area? You need to know if "dental implants [city]" is moving up or down.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">05</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Citation management</h4>
              <p>Does it manage listings on dental directories? Healthgrades, Zocdoc, Vitals, and 90+ directories need consistent NAP data.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="ba-col after">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">What we found</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Content is the biggest gap for most dental practices.</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">Key findings from our evaluation.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Most tools track but don't create</h4>
              <p>9 of 10 tools measure or manage — only theStacc actually produces dental blog content at scale.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Blog content is the missing piece</h4>
              <p>Practices publishing 30 articles monthly see 2–4× faster ranking growth than practices that only optimize their GBP.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Agencies charge 94–97% more for similar output</h4>
              <p>Dental marketing agencies charge $2,000–5,000/month. theStacc delivers more content for $126/month.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- STATS ROW -->
  <section>
    <div class="stats-row">
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">10<span class="accent"></span></div><div class="stat-label">Tools tested for dental SEO</div></div>
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">30<span class="accent"></span></div><div class="stat-label">Articles/month from theStacc — $3.30 each</div></div>
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">$126<span class="accent">/mo</span></div><div class="stat-label">Full blog + GBP bundle with theStacc</div></div>
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">24<span class="accent">h</span></div><div class="stat-label">Time to first article with theStacc</div></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- RANKED LIST -->
  <section class="problem-section" id="ranked-list">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">The full ranked list</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">10 SEO tools for dentists, <span class="accent">ranked by what gets new patients.</span></h2>
      <p>Each entry: rank, name, price, who it fits, one-paragraph verdict, pros, and one honest con.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="service-1">
      <div class="ba-col after" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#1 · WINNER · $99/MO BLOG · $49/MO LOCAL</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">theStacc — Best for automated dental blog content and GBP posting</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For any dental practice that wants to publish consistently without hiring a writer or agency.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">theStacc publishes 30 blog articles monthly on dental topics patients actually search — implant costs, whitening options, emergency dental care, braces vs. Invisalign — plus 30 GBP posts monthly. Dental-specific article topics are researched from actual patient search data. Consistent daily GBP activity signals relevance to Google. At $126/month bundled, it's the most affordable option for this volume of content anywhere.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✓</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Automated content — zero writing from you</h4>
              <p>Dental-specific topics researched and published without any involvement from the practice. 360 articles per year, compounding indefinitely.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✓</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Price: ~$3.30 per article at the bundle rate</h4>
              <p>Dental marketing agencies charge $100–300 per article. Freelancers charge $50–200. theStacc delivers at a fraction of the cost, automatically.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✓</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Integrates with WordPress, Webflow, Ghost, and custom sites</h4>
              <p>Publishes directly to whatever CMS your dental website runs on. No manual uploads.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✗</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Honest con: no review management, rank tracking, or citations</h4>
              <p>theStacc handles content. For tracking and review generation, you'll want to pair it with BrightLocal ($39/mo) and — if patient volume is high — Birdeye ($299/mo).</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <div style="margin-top: 24px;">
          <a href="/checkout/" class="btn btn-primary"><span>Start the $1 trial <span class="arrow">→</span></span></a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="service-2" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#2 · FREE</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Google Business Profile — Best free foundation for dental SEO</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">The first thing every dental practice should claim and optimize before spending on any other tool.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">GBP is free and controls your appearance in local 3-pack results for "dentist near me" searches. All features — photo uploads, service categories, review responses, basic insights — are available to every verified practice at no cost. The downside is that everything is manual. No automation, no scheduling, no content suggestions.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Completely free — no paid tiers</h4><p>Every dental practice should claim and complete their GBP before investing in any paid tool.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Controls local 3-pack visibility</h4><p>Without an optimized GBP, no paid tool can get you into the Map Pack for "dentist near me."</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: manual everything</h4><p>Posts, photos, responses — all manual. Pair with theStacc to automate GBP posting without the ongoing time commitment.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="service-3" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#3 · $39–59/MO PER LOCATION</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">BrightLocal — Best local rank tracking suite for dental practices</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For practices that want to track exactly where they rank across their area and catch citation problems early.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">BrightLocal's geo-grid Map shows your visibility across your entire service area — not just one zip code. GBP audit identifies optimization gaps. Citation auditing catches inconsistencies across dental directories including Healthgrades, Zocdoc, and Vitals. Review monitoring across multiple platforms. Competitor benchmarking for local keywords. The most complete local tracking suite at this price.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Geo-grid shows ranking across the full service area</h4><p>See exactly where you're visible and where competitors are beating you neighborhood by neighborhood.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Citation auditing across dental directories</h4><p>Catches NAP inconsistencies on Healthgrades, Zocdoc, Vitals, and 50+ other directories.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: no content creation</h4><p>BrightLocal shows you the ranking problem; theStacc fixes it. Use them together.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="service-4" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#4 · FROM $299/MO</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Birdeye — Best for patient review generation and management</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For high-volume practices that need automated review collection after every patient visit.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Birdeye automates post-visit review requests via text and email, routes patients directly to Google or Healthgrades, and uses AI to draft responses. Review monitoring across 150+ sites. Sentiment analysis. Competitive benchmarking. If your practice sees 15+ patients daily, automated review requests can generate 20–40 new Google reviews monthly — which directly moves Map Pack rankings.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Automated post-visit review requests</h4><p>Captures patient satisfaction at the right moment — right after a successful appointment.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Routes to Google, Healthgrades, or Yelp directly</h4><p>No friction for the patient. More reviews actually get completed.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: $299/month base price requires patient volume to justify</h4><p>Only makes sense if you're seeing 15+ patients daily. Smaller practices get similar results from manual review requests at zero cost.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="service-5" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#5 · FROM $130/MO</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Semrush — Best for deep dental keyword research (overkill for most)</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For dental marketing agencies or large group practices with a dedicated SEO person on staff.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Semrush has the largest keyword database available and deep competitor analysis. The Keyword Magic Tool contains billions of keywords. Site audits cover 140+ technical SEO checks. Backlink analysis and monitoring. Content optimization scores. The problem is the learning curve and the price: $130/month is hard to justify for a single-location practice without a dedicated marketing person.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Keyword Magic Tool with billions of dental keywords</h4><p>Deep competitor analysis showing ranking opportunities your practice hasn't targeted yet.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>140+ technical SEO checks in the site audit</h4><p>Catches the technical issues that quietly suppress rankings.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: overkill for most dental practices</h4><p>$130/month with a steep learning curve requires a dedicated marketing person to use effectively. SE Ranking delivers 80% of the value at 40% of the price.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="service-6" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#6 · $52/MO + LOCAL ADD-ONS</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">SE Ranking — Best affordable full SEO suite for dental practices</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For practices with in-house marketing who want keyword research, rank tracking, and audits without paying Semrush prices.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">SE Ranking delivers keyword research with local search volume data, technical site audits, competitor analysis, and local listing management as an add-on — at 40% less than Semrush. The AI writer is included but produces generic content that needs dental editing. Local features require a paid add-on, so budget $9–23/month per location on top of the base price.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Full SEO suite at a reasonable price</h4><p>Keyword research, rank tracking, competitor analysis, and site audits — 40% cheaper than Semrush.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>White-label reporting for multi-location dental groups</h4><p>Useful if you manage several practice locations or work with a dental marketing agency.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: local features are paid add-ons</h4><p>Local SEO features aren't included in the base price. Per-location add-ons stack up quickly for multi-location practices.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="service-7" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#7 · FROM $25/MO</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Whitespark — Best for dental directory citations</h3>
